			<p rend="align(center)">COPY</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Dec. 31. 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I send you again a few subscribers to the &#8220;Occident&#8221;<lb/> which I have procured since my last of the <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst.</p>
			<p></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I also send you 8 copies of the &#8220;Alta California&#8221; and the &#8220;Whig&#8221;&#44; which<lb/> contains several items of discussion upon the observance of the <date>Sabbath</date> &#38;c&#44;<lb/> by the perusal of which&#44; you will notice that we do not allow our Religion to<lb/> be slandered&#44; even out here on these Western shores&#44; &#38; are always ready to<lb/> defend our proud and sacred Faith. You&#39;ll read the articles &#40;I marked them<lb/> with a black rounding&#41; &#38; form then your own idea about them. There has nothing<lb/> else&#44; concerning Jewish affairs&#44; transpired to my knowledge&#59; I shall always<lb/> endeavor to keep you posted up on any thing of any importance to you&#44; that<lb/> may occur here&#44; &#38; which may serve as interesting news in your Occident.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The Rainy Season is very severe this year&#44; beyond all expectations&#44; &#38; it is for<lb/> that reason that Merchants did fail in laying in sufficient supplies for<lb/> the winter&#44; and the consequence is in some mines&#44; that miners have to suffer<lb/> very much for want of provisions. For all other local affairs I refer you to<lb/> the Papers.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I enjoy&#44; thank God&#44; good health &#38; hope you may enjoy the same Blessing&#59;<lb/> but Business has moderated greatly&#44; yet we console ourselves with bright<lb/> prospects.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Let me soon hear from you again. Accept the best wishes for your<lb/> Health and Happiness</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">from</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">&#40;signed&#41;&#160;&#160;<persName role="author">C. H. Meyer</persName></p>
			<p></p>
			<p>N. B. <persName>Mr. Roggenburger</persName> &#38; Family<lb/> desire their kind regards to you.</p>
          
        </body>
